                  <div id="innerbodycontent" class="row nolayout"><div class="offset1 span10">
            <div id="sm-cog-elements" class="noprint"></div>
            <div class="allset-page-heading"><h1>Reference:Boya Chinese Lower Intermediate 1 (博雅汉语准中级加速篇)</h1></div>
            <!-- subtitle -->
            <div id="contentSub" ><span class="mw-redirectedfrom">(Redirected from <a href="https://resources.allsetlearning.com/gramwiki/?title=Boya_Chinese_Lower_Intermediate_1_(%E5%8D%9A%E9%9B%85%E6%B1%89%E8%AF%AD%E5%87%86%E4%B8%AD%E7%BA%A7%E5%8A%A0%E9%80%9F%E7%AF%87)&amp;redirect=no" class="mw-redirect" title="Boya Chinese Lower Intermediate 1 (博雅汉语准中级加速篇)">Boya Chinese Lower Intermediate 1 (博雅汉语准中级加速篇)</a>)</span></div>
            <!-- /subtitle -->
                        <div id="mw-content-text" lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr"><div class="mw-parser-output"><p><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.amazon.com/gp/product/7301075308/ref%3das_li_ss_tl?ie=UTF8&amp;tag=allset-20&amp;linkCode=as2&amp;camp=217145&amp;creative=399373&amp;creativeASIN=7301075308"><img class="alignright" src="https&#58;//images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/I/51DEvFOzxTL._SL500_AA300_.jpg" /></a>
</p><p><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.amazon.com/gp/product/7301075308/ref%3das_li_ss_tl?ie=UTF8&amp;tag=allset-20&amp;linkCode=as2&amp;camp=217145&amp;creative=399373&amp;creativeASIN=7301075308">Boya Chinese Lower Intermediate 1 (博雅汉语准中级加速篇) </a> by Li Xiaoqi
</p>
<blockquote><p>Boya Chinese is compiled by a group of experienced teachers who teach Chinese as second language. It is divided into four levels: elementary, pre-intermediate, intermediate and advanced. There are altogether 9 books in the set which suits the four-year college study or any short-term and long-term classes. The elementary level is in two volumes of 50 lessons for beginners and covers about 1,000 words. Finishing it will ensure the students to reach level 3 of HSK. The pre-intermediate level comprises two volumes. It suits students with 1,000-3000 vocabulary. It focuses on trainings of depiction, narration, explanation and discussion. Finishing this level, the students will pass HSK test of level 5-6. The intermediate level has two volumes and is suitable for students who have 3,000-5,000 words. The contents are vivid and include a wide selection of topics. The vocabulary has very detailed notes with carefully selected examples. This level is compatible with HSK level 7-8. The advanced level is for students who master more than 5,000 words. The advanced level has three volumes and contains about 8,000-word vocabulary and focuses on identifying synonyms, explaining common sentence patterns and difficult words. There are ample exercises and interesting readings after each lesson. Finishing this level enables the students to pass HSK level 11 tests.</p></blockquote>
<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Grammar_Points_by_Chapter">Grammar Points by Chapter</span></h2>
<ol><li>Lesson 1
<ul><li><a href="Separable_verb" title="Separable verb"> "离合词" (Separable disyllabic verbs) </a></li>
<li><a href="&quot;Not_only…_but_also&quot;_with_&quot;bujin&quot;" class="mw-redirect" title="&quot;Not only… but also&quot; with &quot;bujin&quot;"> "不仅….而且" (Not only...but also) </a></li>
<li><a href="A_softer_&quot;but&quot;" class="mw-redirect" title="A softer &quot;but&quot;"> "不过" (However) </a></li>
<li><a href="Expressing_&quot;more_and_more&quot;_with_&quot;yue…_yue…&quot;" class="mw-redirect" title="Expressing &quot;more and more&quot; with &quot;yue… yue…&quot;"> "越来越" (More and more) </a></li></ul></li>
<li>Lesson 2
<ul><li>"尤其" （Particularly)</li>
<li><a href="&quot;Not_at_all&quot;" class="mw-redirect" title="&quot;Not at all&quot;"> "一...也不"（没）(Not at all) </a></li>
<li>"好好儿" (Very good/well)</li>
<li>"挺...的" (Very)</li></ul></li>
<li>Lesson 3
<ul><li>"替" In place of</li>
<li>"曾经" (Once (in the past))</li>
<li><a href="Comparisons_with_&quot;buru&quot;" title="Comparisons with &quot;buru&quot;">"不如" (Not as good as)</a></li>
<li><a href="&quot;Due_to…&quot;_with_&quot;youyu&quot;" class="mw-redirect" title="&quot;Due to…&quot; with &quot;youyu&quot;"> "由于" (As a result of) </a></li></ul></li>
<li>Lesson 4
<ul><li>"不一定" (Not necessarily)</li>
<li><a href="&quot;Both…_and…&quot;_with_&quot;ji...you&quot;" class="mw-redirect" title="&quot;Both… and…&quot; with &quot;ji...you&quot;"> "既...又" (Both...and) </a></li>
<li>"左右" (About)</li>
<li>"地方" (Literal and abstract place)</li></ul></li>
<li>Lesson 5
<ul><li><a href="&quot;Although&quot;_with_&quot;jinguan&quot;" class="mw-redirect" title="&quot;Although&quot; with &quot;jinguan&quot;"> "尽管...,可（是）(Even though...but) </a></li>
<li><a href="Result_complement_&quot;-qilai&quot;" class="mw-redirect" title="Result complement &quot;-qilai&quot;"> "起来"(Complement denoting the start of an action) </a></li>
<li>"...不了" (Complement denoting impossibility)</li>
<li><a href="Sequencing_with_&quot;xian&quot;_and_&quot;zai&quot;" title="Sequencing with &quot;xian&quot; and &quot;zai&quot;">"先...,然后...,(最后...) (First..., then..., (finally...))</a></li></ul></li>
<li>Lesson 6
<ul><li><a href="&quot;Always&quot;_with_&quot;conglai&quot;" class="mw-redirect" title="&quot;Always&quot; with &quot;conglai&quot;"> "从来"(All along) </a></li>
<li><a href="Expressing_&quot;rather&quot;_with_&quot;bijiao&quot;" title="Expressing &quot;rather&quot; with &quot;bijiao&quot;"> "比较"(Quite) </a></li>
<li><a href="Expressing_purpose_with_&quot;weile&quot;" title="Expressing purpose with &quot;weile&quot;"> "为了"(In order to) </a></li></ul></li>
<li>Lesson 7
<ul><li>"感兴趣"(Be interested in)</li>
<li>"相当" (Quite)</li>
<li><a href="Comparing_&quot;genben&quot;_and_&quot;daodi&quot;" title="Comparing &quot;genben&quot; and &quot;daodi&quot;">"根本"( Completely, at all)</a></li>
<li>"不一会儿"( In no time at all)</li>
<li><a href="Rhetorical_questions_with_&quot;nandao&quot;" title="Rhetorical questions with &quot;nandao&quot;"> "难道" (Used to form rhetorical sentences) </a></li>
<li>[Before and after with "zhiqian" and "zhihou"|"之后、之前、之间" (Before, after, between)]]</li></ul></li>
<li>Lesson 8
<ul><li>"连忙"(Hurriedly, quickly)</li>
<li>"不好意思"(Sorry)</li>
<li><a href="&quot;Although&quot;_with_&quot;jinguan&quot;" class="mw-redirect" title="&quot;Although&quot; with &quot;jinguan&quot;"> "尽管"(Even though) </a></li></ul></li>
<li>Lesson 9
<ul><li><a href="Expressing_Various_Aspects_with_&quot;yi_fangmian&quot;" class="mw-redirect" title="Expressing Various Aspects with &quot;yi fangmian&quot;">"…方面"(Limiting scope to a particular aspect)</a></li>
<li>"动词 + 上"(To denote an action has started and is continuing with the complement 上)</li>
<li>"当时、当年"(That time, that year)</li></ul></li>
<li>Lesson 10
<ul><li><a href="Comparing_&quot;genju&quot;_and_&quot;ju&quot;" title="Comparing &quot;genju&quot; and &quot;ju&quot;">"根据"(According)</a></li>
<li>"作为" (To be as)</li>
<li>"故意"(Deliberately)</li>
<li>"弄"(To do)</li></ul></li>
<li>Lesson 11
<ul><li>"动词 + 得起/不起" (Using 得起 to denote lacking the time or money to complete an action)</li>
<li><a href="Result_complement_&quot;-qilai&quot;#Expressing_an_initial_judgement" class="mw-redirect" title="Result complement &quot;-qilai&quot;">"动词 + 起来" (Using the complement 起来 to make judgments)</a></li>
<li>"肯" (Willing to)</li>
<li><a href="&quot;As_long_as&quot;_with_&quot;zhiyao&quot;" class="mw-redirect" title="&quot;As long as&quot; with &quot;zhiyao&quot;"> "只要…就" (As long as…so) </a></li>
<li>"不得不"(To have to)</li>
<li><a href="Using_&quot;yi...wei&quot;" class="mw-redirect" title="Using &quot;yi...wei&quot;">"以…为主"(Take something as priority)</a></li></ul></li>
<li>Lesson 12
<ul><li><a href="Emphasizing_a_negation_with_&quot;bing&quot;" title="Emphasizing a negation with &quot;bing&quot;">"并不 + 动词/形容词" (Negating verbs and adjectives with 并不)</a></li>
<li>"往往" (Frequently)</li>
<li><a href="The_&quot;if&quot;_sandwich_pattern" class="mw-redirect" title="The &quot;if&quot; sandwich pattern">"…的话" (Expressing if with the structure …的话)</a></li></ul></li>
<li>Lesson 13
<ul><li><a href="Expressing_“any&quot;_with_&quot;renhe&quot;" class="mw-redirect" title="Expressing “any&quot; with &quot;renhe&quot;"> "任何" (Any) </a></li>
<li>"否则" (Otherwise)</li>
<li><a href="&quot;er&quot;_used_to_explain_contrasting_ideas" class="mw-redirect" title="&quot;er&quot; used to explain contrasting ideas"> "而" </a></li>
<li><a href="Expressing_&quot;to_make_certain&quot;_with_&quot;qianwan&quot;" title="Expressing &quot;to make certain&quot; with &quot;qianwan&quot;">"千万"</a></li></ul></li>
<li>Lesson 14
<ul><li><a href="Emphatic_adverb_&quot;ke&quot;" title="Emphatic adverb &quot;ke&quot;"> "可" (Adding emphasis with 可) </a></li>
<li><a href="&quot;If…,_then…&quot;_with_&quot;ruguo…,_jiu…&quot;" class="mw-redirect" title="&quot;If…, then…&quot; with &quot;ruguo…, jiu…&quot;"> "如果…就"（if…then）</a></li>
<li>"不…不…"</li>
<li>"动词/形容词 + 不 + 补语"</li></ul></li>
<li>Lesson 15
<ul><li><a href="Comparing_&quot;zongsuan&quot;_and_“zhongyu&quot;" title="Comparing &quot;zongsuan&quot; and “zhongyu&quot;"> "终于" (Finally) </a></li>
<li><a href="&quot;Therefore&quot;_with_&quot;yinci&quot;" class="mw-redirect" title="&quot;Therefore&quot; with &quot;yinci&quot;"> "因此" (Because) </a></li>
<li>"再 + 形容词" (No matter how)</li></ul></li>
<li>Lesson 16
<ul><li><a href="&quot;As_long_as&quot;_with_&quot;zhiyao&quot;" class="mw-redirect" title="&quot;As long as&quot; with &quot;zhiyao&quot;"> "自从" (Ever since) </a></li>
<li><a href="&quot;As_much_as_possible&quot;_with_&quot;jinliang&quot;" class="mw-redirect" title="&quot;As much as possible&quot; with &quot;jinliang&quot;"> "尽量" (To the best of one’s ability) </a></li>
<li>"临" (Just before)</li>
<li>"…得要命" (Complement meaning extremely)</li>
<li><a href="The_&quot;However&quot;_Adverb_&quot;que&quot;" class="mw-redirect" title="The &quot;However&quot; Adverb &quot;que&quot;"> "却" (However) </a></li>
<li>"先后" (Successively)</li></ul></li></ol>
